  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (01325bc 2022-08-03T00:04:34.894101923Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge fmt\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nAfter running `forge fmt` the comment of the first members of a struct is always one indentation too shallow:\r\n```solidity\r\n    struct MyStruct {\r\n    // first 1\r\n    // first 2\r\n        uint256 field1;\r\n        // second\r\n        uint256 field2;\r\n    }\r\n```\r\nIt doesn't matter if the comment is single- or multi-line, the entire comment has invalid indentation. All the following fields are correctly indented.",
